- In the context of machine learning, a model's performance metric could be a measure of its accuracy or efficiency (e.g., accuracy score, F1 score, mean squared error); 
- The last evaluation date refers to the most recent date a model's performance was assessed; 
- The deployment date represents the date a model was put into production or use; 
- The model type could be classification, regression, clustering, etc.; 
- A version hierarchy implies a lineage of model versions, with each version building upon the previous one; 
- Average metric value and number of predictions are used as proxies for model performance and usage respectively.
